insta_description:
Isomeris arborea: California Cleome (Bladderpod). Yellow flowers & fruits that resemble paper lanterns with dry seeds that rattle inside. Strange odor (burnt popcorn). Thrives on SoCal coastal bluffs (salt spray) and  tolerates high alkaline soil and in extremely dry conditions. Evergreen shrub (4ft high) that can survive in harsh areas.

Making these posts to help remember all these native species for work, plus they're pretty kewl :P

#plants #ecology #botany #environment #restoration #californiacleome #california #native #loscerritoswetlands #longbeach #sealbeach #la #california

insta_description:
Distichlis spicata: known by several common names, including seashore saltgrass, inland saltgrass, and desert saltgrass. Extremely salt tolerant and hardy. Widespread across the Americas and naturalized on other continents. Rids excess salts by secreting it onto its surfaces.  Kawaiisu Indians were able to make salt blocks by scraping off the salt.

insta_description:
Battling cancer through my early twenties gave me one lasting effect which I consider both a blessing and curse. It made me view each day as such a fleeting gift, that sometimes I run myself ragged trying to get as much out of each one as I possibly can. I exhaust myself all the time with the feeling of "Tomorrow isn't promised". Which is how I will likely feel today, as I'm awake at 4am preparing to tramp up Mt Taranaki (an 8-10 hour expected completion) in less than great weather, then hop in the van to drive 5 hours to Wellington so I can catch the early ferry to the south island the next morning in order to start my first day of work ü§£ üì∏ taken by my new Maori friend, Ahene (translates to Angel, very fitting) at Te Rere o Noke (Dawson's Falls) #nofilter
#dontworry #ihavehikingpoles
#locoamerican #solotraveler #wildnewzealand #mttaranaki #ospreypacks #backpackersworld  #nothingbadsgonnahappentoday #andshesdopetoo

insta_description:
One of my favorite days so far was driving the Forgotten World Hwy from Taumarunui towards Taranaki. Its New Zealands oldest heritage trail, and the whole winding way is breathtaking and raw. This is Moki Tunnel, or "Hobbit's  Hole", a 180-metre tunnel which has fossilized giant crabs within its walls! The drive took me a solid day as there were so many amazing spots to go off road along the way for waterfalls, the gorge, Two lavender farms, and the Whanganui¬†river. Sheeesh! Gonna have to hit it again when I get back up north, and give myself a couple days! ü§†ü¶Ä‚úå

insta_description:
üì£üì£üì£ Quick break from baby goat posts because April is National Child Abuse Prevention Month!¬†üì£üì£üì£ As a Court Appointed Special Advocate, I'm a sworn officer of the court appointed by a juvenile court judge to advocate for children who are living in foster care as a result of abuse or neglect. It is critical for success that every child has at least ONE consistent and caring adult in their life. Especially for children who are dependents of the court, that one person can really impact the trajectory of the child's life.

This is one way I've chosen to serve my community and help prevent child abuse or neglect. I'm encouraging my friends to¬†find an opportunity to mentor a child or parent, advocate¬†for family friendly policies, or donate time or money to child-serving organizations. It only takes one person to change a life! 
If you have any questions about the CASA national or local programs, please message me! It's a really amazing way to serve foster children and youth. Also, @sierraforeverfamilies has a *Wonder*ful mentoring program for children living in foster care, if you're in Sacramento County! ‚ù§üå±‚ù§ #casa #nationalchildabusepreventionmonth #childadvocate #california

insta_description:
September is Ovarian Cancer Awareness month! 
I don't have any teal to wear, but I am a survivor of a long and hard fight with this disease. While I'm grateful for the infinite amount of strength, perspective, and zest for life that I gained from my years fighting this cancer, I wish it hadn't happened. I wish I could have my womb back. I wish no one had to suffer this loss. Surviving means I am here to spread awareness in hopes that less women will suffer or lose precious life to this silent killer. 
Ovarian cancer is silent because the early symptoms often go unnoticed. The late stage symptoms can easily be confused with non threatening illnesses, as was the case for me. This unfortunate loss of detection time can mean losing your  reproductive organs, or losing your life. There is no easy treatment once you hit late stage, and the chance of survival becomes devastatingly low, while chance of reoccurrence becomes heartbreakingly high.

Ladies, ANYONE with ovaries, PLEASE arm yourself with knowledge, love and know your body, and keep up with your gynecological visits!  Early detection is your greatest power against cancer. ü¶öü¶öü¶ö üì∑ and rejuvenating weekend on high elevation waters üåä@emilywinteryoga 
#ovariancancerawarenessmonth

insta_description:
For anyone out there assuming that every dairy farm pulls babies away from the Dams at birth to "steal milk", this is how @nightingalefarms operates. Our kids are dam raised and we still get plenty of milk for our small batch body product business. Doelings (females) born are kept in the dairy herd to be future milkers, and the bucklings (males) are wethered and kept for the brushing herd to work private property contracts for wildfire mitigation and vegetation management. üêê

Every farm operates differently for different reasons. The great thing about small farms is that you can ASK questions and support a farm or products that match your ethical standards! Most small farms provide tours or will be happy to accommodate a visit for interested consumers. Also, check out farm certifications, you can learn a lot about a farm based on their certs. üêê

A big 2020 goal for Nightingale Farms  is to obtain my Animal Welfare Approved certification. Check out @foodanimalconcernstrust for more information about standards for humane farming! üåøüêÑüåøüêëüåøüêê #goats #farming #animalwelfare #supportsmallfarms #knowyourfarmer #goatmilkgoodness #handmilkedhandmade #nightingalefarms #nevadacounty #california
